<p class="indent3" style="-uslm-lc:I14" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Except as provided in clause (ii), the depreciation deduction allowable under section 167 with respect to any tangible property placed in service after <date date="1986-12-31">December 31, 1986</date>, shall be determined under the alternative system of section 168(g). In the case of property placed in service after <date date="1998-12-31">December 31, 1998</date>, the preceding sentence shall not apply but clause (ii) shall continue to apply.</p>
